  <h1>Rules
  <p>A basic explanation of ladder style tournaments may be found at #
     <a href=http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ladder_tournament>wikipedia</a>.
 <p> The purpose of the Northeastern Ladder is to encourage friendly competition while getting a general idea of everyone’s skill level. Games will take place during our Wednesday meetings. 
  <p>The object of the Ladder is to reach position number one. When you join the ladder, you will start at the bottom. To climb the ladder, you can challenge somebody up to three spots above you. Players must accept a challenge from another player. The players will play a best of 3 set using the APEX rule set. Report the match results to Theo Landegger, either in person or through Facebook. If the higher ranked player wins, the ladder does not change. If the lower ranked player wins, they will take the higher ranked players spot. The loser and all lower players will be shifted down to refill the ladder. For Example: If Fred challenges Bob and wins, the ladder would change as so:
